Advanced Slide Layouts and Features

To make your PowerPoint template more advanced and versatile, consider these enhancements:

Master Slide Variations: Create multiple master slide layouts for different purposes (e.g., title only, title + content, two content columns, quote slide).

Custom Placeholders: Include placeholders for images, charts, tables, and icons that can be easily replaced.

Interactive Elements: Add clickable buttons or navigation links for non-linear presentations.

Consistent Iconography: Use a set of vector icons matching the color theme for bullets, section dividers, and callouts.

Data Visualization Styles: Predefine chart styles (bar, line, pie) with theme colors and fonts.

Animations and Transitions: Subtle, professional animations for text and objects to enhance engagement without distraction.

Accessibility Features: Ensure sufficient color contrast, readable font sizes, and alt text placeholders for images.

